  <a href="https://github.com/eclipse-sisu/sisu-project/releases/tag/milestones%2F0.9.0.M2" class="externalLink">0.9.0.M2</a></p></li>
  <a href="https://github.com/eclipse-sisu/sisu-project/releases/tag/milestones%2F0.9.0.M1" class="externalLink">0.9.0.M1</a></p></li>
  Sisu 0.3.0 has been released!</p></li>
  </ul></section><section><a id="Meaning_of_.E2.80.9CSisu.E2.80.9D"></a>
  <h1>Meaning of &#x201c;Sisu&#x201d;</h1>
  <p><sub>From <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Sisu&amp;oldid=371994592" class="externalLink">https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Sisu&amp;oldid=371994592</a></sub></p>
  <p>Sisu is a Finnish term loosely translated into English as strength of will, determination, perseverance, and acting rationally in the face of adversity. However, the word is widely considered to lack a proper translation into any language. Sisu has been described as being integral to understanding Finnish culture. The literal meaning is equivalent in English to &#x201c;having guts&#x201d;, and the word derives from sisus, which means something inner or interior. However sisu is defined by a long-term element in it; it is not momentary courage, but the ability to sustain an action against the odds. Deciding on a course of action and the sticking to that decision against repeated failures is sisu. It is similar to equanimity, except the forbearance of sisu has a grimmer quality of s
